    "causal_summary": "The F2 clean-close barrier (`reapLeaseChildBeforeRespawn` in `mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs`, shipped in 032/001) decides whether a possibly-dirty DB is handed to a replacement daemon. Its pure helpers (`cleanCloseAfterReap`, `uncleanShutdownMarkerPath`) are unit-tested, but the reap orchestration itself — SIGTERM, the SIGKILL escalation, and the marker-based clean-close determination — had zero live coverage. The only real-process launcher suite (`launcher-lease.vitest.ts`) is entirely `describe.skip`'d as a \"known launcher process lifecycle flake,\" so the safety-critical path was untested.",
